Millie Bobby Brown was among several thousand people stranded on the island of Bali, after a volcano threatened to erupt.

But despite her ordeal, The Stranger Things star was grateful for the staff at the Mulian hotel, and made it a point to thank them in an Instagram post.

The teen originally planned to visit for four days, but her mini excursion turned into a 10-day-long stay.

'I cannot thank you enough!': Millie Bobby Brown, 13
